comments.body:
`SpendBlock` can run before `CheckBlock` (e.g. in `ConnectTip`, `VerifyDB`), so malformed blocks may hit `blockundo.vtxundo.reserve(block.vtx.size() - 1`) without prior validation.

```suggestion
    const auto time_start{SteadyClock::now()};

    // SpendBlock may run before CheckBlock() in some paths (e.g. VerifyDB).
    // Defensively reject structurally invalid blocks here to avoid size_t
    // underflow in blockundo reservation.
    if (block.vtx.empty())
        return state.Invalid(BlockValidationResult::BLOCK_CONSENSUS, "bad-blk-length", "size limits failed");
```

