This feels quite brittle and I could see it causing bugs in the future.

Would it be possible to implement as a callback instead, so that the short scope is forced?

Something like:
```c++
template <typename Callable>
auto AccessCoins(const CTransaction& tx, const Callable& callback) const
{
    std::vector<std::reference_wrapper<const Coin>> coins;
    coins.reserve(tx.vin.size());
    for (const CTxIn& input : tx.vin) {
        coins.emplace_back(AccessCoin(input.prevout));
    }
    return callback(std::span{coins}));
}
```

And used like:
```c++
auto sigop_count = AccessCoins(tx, [&tx](auto&& coins) {
    return GetP2SHSigOpCount(tx, coins);
});

```

