comments.body:
The `high-hash` error means the block failed proof-of-work in `CheckBlockHeader()` before `CheckBlock()` reached the empty-block size check.

So this test is not actually proving that `SpendBlock()` handles empty blocks safely. It only proves that `SpendBlock()` calls `CheckBlock()` and rejects a header with invalid PoW.

That matters because the original risk was an empty block reaching later `SpendBlock()` logic and causing `block.vtx.size() - 1` underflow. If the test fails earlier with `high-hash`, it would still pass even if the empty-block size check path were broken or unreachable.

Suggested change:

<details>
  <summary>diff</summary>

```diff
diff --git a/src/test/validation_chainstate_tests.cpp b/src/test/validation_chainstate_tests.cpp
index 8e8726ce98..9f69b057c6 100644
--- a/src/test/validation_chainstate_tests.cpp
+++ b/src/test/validation_chainstate_tests.cpp
@@ -219,9 +219,13 @@ BOOST_FIXTURE_TEST_CASE(spendblock_rejects_empty_block, TestChain100Setup)
     LOCK(cs_main);
     CBlockIndex* tip = Assert(chainstate.m_chain.Tip());

-    CBlock block;
-    // CheckBlock() rejects empty blocks, ensure it gets run in SpendBlock
-    block.hashPrevBlock = tip->GetBlockHash();
+    CBlock block{CreateBlock({}, CScript{} << OP_TRUE)};
+    // CheckBlock() rejects empty blocks; keep the header otherwise valid so
+    // SpendBlock reaches the size check instead of failing earlier on PoW.
+    block.vtx.clear();
+    block.hashMerkleRoot = BlockMerkleRoot(block);
+    block.nNonce = 0;
+    while (!CheckProofOfWork(block.GetHash(), block.nBits, Params().GetConsensus())) ++block.nNonce;

     CBlockIndex index_dummy{block};
     const uint256 block_hash{block.GetHash()};
@@ -235,7 +239,7 @@ BOOST_FIXTURE_TEST_CASE(spendblock_rejects_empty_block, TestChain100Setup)

     BOOST_CHECK(!chainstate.SpendBlock(block, &index_dummy, view_dummy, state, blockundo));
     BOOST_CHECK(state.IsInvalid());
-    BOOST_CHECK_EQUAL(state.GetRejectReason(), "high-hash");
+    BOOST_CHECK_EQUAL(state.GetRejectReason(), "bad-blk-length");
 }

 BOOST_AUTO_TEST_SUITE_END()
```
